<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.eqdiva.com/guides/hunting.asp">www.eqdiva.com/guides/hunting.asp</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
It's on the EQ Diva website, one of the best bard-specific sites around.  The hunting guide is broken down in 5-level chunks, with guides specific to each zone submitted by players.<br>
<br>
Some of the discussion is bard-specific (e.g., what creatures and where to pull when Bellow kiting) but much of the information is suitable for other classes.  Good tactical advice in some of the guides as well, especially the ones written by Reed Stormwind.<br>
<br>
So, if your'e looking for an alternative to sitting for 2 hours in Highkeep waiting for a spot to open up, check out this guide for advice!<br>
